# Country

1. This model is used to **store country details in the system**.
2. It contains the **country name**.
3. Each country has a unique **ID**.
4. It includes an **active flag** to enable or disable the country.
5. It stores when the country was **created**.
6. It also tracks the **last updated time**.
7. This data is used in **location-related features**.
8. It helps in **dropdowns or address selection**.
9. Only active countries are shown to users.
10. Overall, it manages **country master data**.

---

# ContentTopic

1. This model is used to **store topics for content generation**.
2. Each topic is linked to a **prompt (AI instruction)**.
3. It contains the **topic name and description**.
4. It also stores the **platform (like LinkedIn, etc.)**.
5. The status field shows the **current state of the topic**.
6. Status can be like **Draft, Approved, Scheduled, Published, etc.**
7. It includes an **active flag** to control visibility.
8. It stores when the topic was **created and last updated**.
9. These topics are used to **generate AI content posts**.
10. Overall, it manages **content planning topics in the system**.

---

# ContentPostFile

1. This model is used to **store files related to content posts**.
2. Each file is linked to a **post using post ID**.
3. It stores the **file URL (like image or video link)**.
4. It also keeps the **file name**.
5. It includes an **active flag** to manage file usage.
6. It tracks when the file was **created and updated**.
7. This is used for **media attachments in posts**.
8. Files can be **images, videos, or documents**.
9. Helps in managing **multiple files per post**.
10. Overall, it handles **media storage for content posts**.

---

# ContentPost

1. This model is used to **store actual content posts created by users**.
2. It contains the **user ID who created the post**.
3. It stores the **main content text of the post**.
4. It includes details like **post type and platform**.
5. It also tracks the **status of the post** (draft, published, etc.).
6. The post has a **scheduled date and time**.
7. It includes a **name/title for the post**.
8. It has an **active flag to manage visibility**.
9. It stores **creation and last update timestamps**.
10. Overall, it manages **user-created social media posts**.

---

# ContentManagerAndUser

1. This model is used to **map a content manager to a user**.
2. It stores the **user ID and manager ID**.
3. This defines **who manages whose content**.
4. It helps in **role-based content management**.
5. Managers can **review or control user content**.
6. It includes an **active flag for the relationship**.
7. It tracks when the mapping was **created**.
8. This is useful in **team or organization setup**.
9. Helps assign **responsibility for content approval**.
10. Overall, it manages **user-manager relationships in content workflow**.
